      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted using meshes of 4.2M, 8.7M, and 17.1M hexahedral cells. Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI values between 1.8% and 3.4% for NIH across the five operating points, all below the 5% threshold. The fine-grid solution was selected for all production runs. Asymptotic range check confirmed monotonic convergence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
