      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (NIH and RH index) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint of pump-induced hemolysis and to the regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "NIH and the derived relative hemolysis index RH are the standard regulatory quantities for pump-induced hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance and ISO 10993-4. Both quantities are directly computed from the CFD flow field via the power-law hemolysis model. The QoIs are clinically relevant and are the same quantities used in predicate device comparison, confirming their relevance to the CPB COU decision."
    },
    {
