      "rationale": "Primary in-vitro validation was performed using the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at flow rates of 4–6 L/min and rotational speeds of 3500–5000 RPM, matching the CPB COU envelope. The secondary validation using the NHLBI VAD benchmark dataset at 2500 RPM and normal hematocrit was considered supplementary evidence of solver shear-stress fidelity. The assessment team concluded that the combination of primary and secondary validation activities provides adequate coverage of the COU, though the rotational speed and hematocrit differences in the secondary comparator were noted without formal sensitivity analysis."
