    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-hemolysis-cou1-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lab-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Seven of thirteen credibility factors were assessed and all met or exceeded required levels for MRL 2. Six factors were not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scope for a Class II CPB device. The primary validation result demonstrates NIH predictions within combined uncertainty bounds at three of five operating points, with interpolated coverage at the remaining two. The secondary validation against the NHLBI VAD benchmark dataset provides additional evidence of solver shear-stress fidelity with a KS statistic of 0.087. The assessment team concluded that the CFD model is credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions across the CPB COU envelope and that the RH < 1 acceptance criterion is satisfied at all five operating points. The credibility assessment supports regulatory submission for the Class II CPB device.",
